The Prague public transport (MHD) will introduce, on Wednesday, the chip in their ticketing system
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be inscribed in the history of the Pra<0xC5><0xBE>sk<0xC3><0xBD> Dopravní povrond (Prague Transport Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will board the metro, trams and buses, who, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pockets.
At the moment, the latter is accessible to about one hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard smart card.
