To combat these differences, Mr. Obama's education program particularly supports among so many other topics, "bilingual transitional education" for those who learn English.
However, the question that arises for Obama is whether his desire to achieve a bilingual education that advocates classroom instruction in languages other than English goes beyond his interest in eliminating differences.
