What interested me was to create an intimate atmosphere that allows me to capture with the camera the moments of personality of flamenco stars.”
With the festival "Popular Song of the Mines", Bauer began in 1997 a long journey to photograph singers, guitarists or dancers with a plate camera.
These are portraits that, thanks to the choice of the camera and the material, recall the classic photography.
The implementation of different stylistic means breaks with the classic side of the image, giving it a touch of modernity, this reflects the perception of flamenco according to Bauer: "A music with very traditional roots that evolves and that surprises every day".
It is not about dance or singing in itself, but about the personality and character of the artist who captivates the audience with his art.
The search for the essentials and magic has been the constant of this work that is presented these days at the gallery El Fotómata.
Flamenco stars such as Diego El Cigala, Chano Lobato, Cristina Hoyos, Enrique Morente, El Lebrijano, Antonio Canales, Vicente Amigo, among others, are part of the selection made from about seventy photographed artists.
The project has become an anthology of flamenco, which will soon be published in a book collection of portraits exhibited at the gallery.
Bauer’s passion for portraits led him to repeat the idea two years ago with the “Portraits of Old Sportsmen” (“SportARTproject”).
Although the concepts are different in "Flamenco - people", the photographer admits that he loves photographing people's portraits, getting to know them and being able to enter their lives for a moment more or less.
I think that in photography the portrait is the most difficult genre.
You find yourself in front of people, characters that sometimes you do not know or that leave you only a few minutes to be able to take a photo of them.
Despite these circumstances, as a photographer, I always try to make my ideas come true.”
This collection of portraits of the current flamenco, entitled "Flamenco - people", is on display at the El Fotómata Gallery, located at number 20 de la Rue de la Mata (a street parallel to the People of Hercules) which will be open until next October 16.
