However, it is a confirmed fact that the search terms are not only registered, but in justified cases, they are transmitted to a third party, and in such legal cases, nothing protects the personal rights of Internet users.
The most striking example in recent times is probably the coordinated action against Brazilian pedophiles, during which Google transmitted to the Brazilian government the information it had collected on the public page called Orkut, thus allowing identification.
Human rights-minded Internet users were able to breathe a sigh of relief last May, when Google, arm in arm with the electronic legal protection body EFF, proved its right to the court in front of the FBI. According to the judgment rendered, in the future, Google will still not be obliged by any of the points of the constitution will be able to request information on the nature of the FBI to be disclosed.
