Google’s judgment is therefore quite contradictory: it is whipped by those who fear the transmission of their personal data, because they think that their intimate sphere and private domain suffer from it when they start using Google services. Therefore, they attack them in the spirit of revolt that is manifested against the multinational companies proud of their image.
Meanwhile, the American geek culture and its savages bringing together enthusiasts, activists and enthusiastic computer users who appear in many countries see in Google the next generation of big companies, the “connected corporation”, as opposed to its rival, Microsoft, cataloged as the world’s invader, even if they beat the same ones for Windows, and the goal.
