Open Office, this is the third edition of the "anti-Microsoft" package
This is the day of the release of OpenOffice.org.3.0, the open source suite of personal productivity that aims to touch ever more users, from home to office, professionals to public administration, offering a free alternative to the most famous Microsoft Office.
Following nearly a year of ISO work by volunteer developers, supervised by SUN Microsystems, the new Open Office package is shown to the general public with various novelties: from the welcome screen, and the revised and become less austere interface, to other more important ones, such as the compatibility born for the latest version, the standard Mac OS support and the new OS format.
Open Office has paid particular attention to the interaction with the Office 2007 suite, and it is indeed possible to open documents with the new Microsoft extension (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx.)
Also interesting are some module-specific features, such as the one that allows you to reduce the size of PowerPoint presentations, useful for example, to send them by email, or to import PDF files into the graphics development module, preserving the original appearance of the page.
Also on this front, it is possible to create "Hybrid PDF" documents that combine the typical Adobe format graphic with elements of a spreadsheet or a text editor.
Collaboration between multiple people is an element that has had various improvements within the applications: in the spreadsheet, various users can intervene, avoiding conflicts on changes, in the drafting of texts, because each contributor is assigned a color of comments for better recognition in the revision phase.
Some companies are even working to bring certain OpenOffice features to the web (on the cloud, on the cloud), and in the coming weeks, they are expected to issue the final result.
The Italian version can be downloaded at http://en.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.htmlet and is added to the English version that was on the mirror since Friday.
In addition to Windows and Mac OS, the suite is as usual also available for the Linux operating system.
On request, the installation CD can be shipped at home or at the workplace.
And if the theme of freelancing can be a way to spread it in the homes, it is precisely in business, that Open Office later tries the big challenge, already relying on various projects carried out in the public administration and schools.
Not to mention the realities that offer a training, consultation and support service, ideal for small and medium-sized enterprises, which could also open up to business prospects.
Open Office consists of five main modules: Writer, for Word equivalent video writing; Calc, is the spreadsheet that aims to replace Excel; Impress, for rival PowerPoint presentations; Dbase, such as the famous Access, is the program that allows you to work on the databases; finally Drwa is the graphics module.
Goal for 2008, reach 5 million downloads, and considering that today there are almost 3 million and 600 miles, it is likely that with the release of the new version, you can even exceed the expected number
Kohl, too, is positive, this is the fourth case of doping.
New case of positivity in the last Tour de France: this is the Austrian team Gerolsteiner, Bernhard Kohl, qualified third, and winner of the jersey of the best climber.
It is the website of the daily L'Equipe that reports the news.
At the age of 26, Kohl is the fourth positive cyclist in Cera, the third generation Epo, after the Italians Riccardo Riccco and Leonardo Piepoli, and the German Stefan Schumacher, also from Gerolsteiner.
The blood tests performed on Kohl samples are part of those carried out in recent weeks by the laboratories of Lausanne and Chatenay-Malabry.
If the counter-analysis confirms the positivity at Cera, the Austrian will lose his third place in the Tour and will have to wait two years for elimination.
The news of Kohl's positivity to the third generation EPO, was confirmed by the head of the French anti-doping agency, Pierre Bordry, who communicated to the Associated Press, having notified the positivity to the Austrian authorities.
The 26-year-old Austrian placed on the podium behind Spanish Carlos Sastre and American Cadel Evans, picking up the best climber's pea jersey.
